    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1849-08-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1849-08-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="247" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d247">
                <head>
                    <seg type="margin">[697]</seg> *<hi rend="italic">Commandant
                                        <persName type="from">Newton</persName>, United States Navy,
                                    to Lieutenant-Commandant <persName type="to">Farrand</persName>,
                                    United States Navy.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Handed with sealed orders.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <dateline>
                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1849-08-28">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">August</hi> 28, 1849</date>.</dateline>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Proceed to sea at once with the United
                                States schooner Flirt, under your command, and be governed by the
                                accompanying <hi rend="italic">sealed orders</hi>, which you are
                                expressly enjoined not to open until after you have crossed the bar
                                and discharged the pilot.</p>
                <p>I am, very respectfully, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <list>
                            <item>JOHN THOMAS NEWTON<lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Commandant.</hi>
                            </item>
                            <item>Lieutenant-Commandant <hi rend="smallcaps">Eben
                                                Farrand.</hi>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
